OL,3,CBritain facing a water scarcity
OL,4,Ccrisis. What is being done to prevent
OL,5,Cit?
OL,7,FMany parts of England are already
OL,8,Fexperiencing water shortages. England
OL,9,Fas a whole has had its driest spring
OL,10,Fsince 1929. Reservoirs are running
OL,11,Flow. In the North West of England, a
OL,12,Fdrought has been declared.
OL,14,FEngland and Wales' reservoirs have
OL,15,Fcapacity to hold 1,600 gigalitres of
OL,16,Fwater. To put that in context,
OL,17,FAustralia, a much drier country, has
OL,18,F84,000 gigalitres of storage capacity.
